{"id": "duc04-testb-16:13#39", "contents": "Chuck Schumer, a member of the House Judiciary Committee, is conducting an impeachment investigation and has publicly stated that the president deserves a lesser punishment, such as censure or reprimand, rather than impeachment. Schumer's stance on the issue has led to speculation about whether he will use it as a campaign issue in his upcoming election. His media adviser, Hank Morris, has hinted that impeachment could become a significant issue, suggesting that Schumer's opponent, Senator D'Amato, is out of touch with the people of New York by not sharing his opinion on the matter."}
